<h1 class="post-title">About Us?</h1>

<h3>Welcome to By the Campfire</h3>

<p class="post-content">
    This is a multi-authored collection of random literature, stories, and musings by a close-knit group of friends, namely: Ned, Miguel, and Dwight. Ned decided to build this site since he knows the specific kind of "literature" required to put a web page together (coding).
    Here, you will read posts from the three of us (or more, if anyone wants to join!). We have all agreed to use our pen names rather than our real identities.
    If you'd like to join us around the bonfire, kindly disturb @ned and send him a message by clicking this link.
</p>

<div id="author-list">Loading...
    <img src="${a.avatar}" alt="${a.name}" />
</div>

<script>
  async function loadAuthors() {
    const res = await fetch('/.netlify/functions/get-authors');
    const authors = await res.json();
    document.getElementById('author-list').innerHTML =
      authors.map(a => `<span>${a.name}
    <img src="${a.avatar}" alt="${a.name}" />
        
        </span>`).join(', ');
  }
  loadAuthors();
</script>